== prompt 0 :: type=typescript-example/src/math.ts.Counter :: pass=type_summary ==
You are analyzing a TypeScript type named Counter to summarize what it represents.

```
export class Counter {
    private n: number;

    constructor() {
        this.n = 0;
    }

    /** Increments the counter and returns the new value. */
    bump(): number {
        this.n = add(this.n, 1);
        return this.n;
    }

    /** Returns the current counter value. */
    value(): number {
        return this.n;
    }
}
```

Documentation: Counter accumulates bumps into a running total.

Methods:
- `constructor(): Counter` — Counter accumulates bumps into a running total.
- `(method) bump(): number` — Increments the counter and returns the new value.
- `(method) value(): number` — Returns the current counter value.

